Chipotle Chicken and Rice Bowls

Ingredients
1.0 Unit(s): Sweet Potato
1.0 Unit(s): Yellow Onion
2.0 Unit(s): Scallions
1.0 Unit(s): Roma Tomato
1.0 Unit(s): Lime
1.0 Tablespoon(s): Southwest Spice
0.5 Cup(s): Jasmine Rice
4.0 Tablespoon(s): Sour Cream
1.0 Teaspoon(s): Chipotle Powder
10.0 Ounce(s): Chicken Cutlets

Instructions
Step 1: Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.
Step 2: Dice sweet potato into 1/2 inch pieces. Halve, peel, and cut onion into 1/2 inch thick wedges. Trim and thinly slice scallions, separating whites from greens. Dice tomato. Zest and quarter Lime.
Step 3: Toss sweet potato on one side of baking sheet with a drizzle of oil, half the southwest spice, salt and pepper. Toss Onion on empty side with a drizzle of oil, salt, and pepper.
Step 4: Roast on top rack, tossing halfway, for 25 minutes.
Step 5: Meanwhile heat a drizzle of oil in a small pot over medium high hea. Add Scallion whites and cook for 1 minute.
Step 6: Add rice, 3/4 cup water, and a large pinch of salt. Bring to a boil then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook til tender, 15-18 minutes. Keep covered off heat til ready to serve.
Step 7: While rice cooks, in a small bowl combine sour cream a squeeze of lime juice, and a pinch of chipotle powder. Stir in water 1 tsp at a time for drizzling consistency. Salt, Pepper, and additional chipotle powder to taste.
Step 9: Pat chicken dry with paper towels and season with remaining southwest spice, salt, and pepper.
Step 8: Heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, 3-5 minutes a side. Transfer to a cutting board to let rest for 5 minutes while making salsa. Cut crosswise once rested.
Step 9: In a second small bowl combine tomato, scallion greens, a squeeze of lime, salt and pepper.
Step 10: Fluff rice with fork, add squeeze of lime, salt, pepper, and lime zest.
Step 11: Divide rice between bowls. Top with veggies, chicken, and salsa. Drizzle with chipotle crema. Serve with remaining lime on the side.
